      "name": "Hironoshin Furuhashi",
      "bio": "Hironoshin Furuhashi was an iconic Japanese freestyle swimmer, distinguished as the 'flying fish of Fujiyama.' In the late 1940s, he broke several world records and is credited with reviving Japanese swimming following World War II. Furuhashi remained influential in the sport as president of the Japan Swimming Federation, and played a key role in bringing the 1991 World Aquatics Championships to Fukuoka, Japan. He is remembered for both his athletic achievements and his leadership in the world of swimming."
